<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-2118] Prepared SQL query does not handle collection-valued parameter where collection is empty</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-2118</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In PreparedQueryImpl.setCollectionValuedParameter, we do a &apos;%n&apos; but don&apos;t check for n==0, as can be seen here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    private void setCollectionValuedParameter(Map&amp;lt;Integer,Object&amp;gt; result, &lt;br/&gt;
        Collection values, int[] indices, Object param) {&lt;br/&gt;
        int n = values.size();&lt;br/&gt;
        Object[] array = values.toArray();&lt;br/&gt;
        if (n &amp;gt; indices.length || indices.length%n != 0) {    &amp;lt;---------------------line 389 in 2.0.x&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;When n==0, the following exception will occur:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception data: java.lang.ArithmeticException: divide by zero&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.openjpa.jdbc.kernel.PreparedQueryImpl.setCollectionValuedParameter(PreparedQueryImpl.java:389)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will upload a test to reproduce this issue and a proposed fix in the next day or two.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
